"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.1.2.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.1.2.2</span> 标题：钥匙（key）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：מַפְתֵּחַ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：mafteach)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:25\">JDG 3:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:22\">ISA 22:22</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：κλείς</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：kleis)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:19\">MAT 16:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:52\">LUK 11:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:18\">REV 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:7\">REV 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:1\">REV 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1\">REV 20:1</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0404_key.jpg\" alt=\"罗马时代钥匙\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">罗马时代钥匙 (© Hermann Junghans, CC BY-SA 3.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>钥匙是用来锁门和开门的工具。古代的钥匙通常比现在的钥匙要大很多。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0405_keys.jpg\" alt=\"古罗马钥匙（鲁芬霍芬考古公园（Archaeological park Ruffenhofen）: 利姆塞姆（Limeseum））\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">古罗马钥匙（鲁芬霍芬考古公园（Archaeological park Ruffenhofen）: 利姆塞姆（Limeseum）） (© Wolfgang Sauber, CC BY-SA 3.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>钥匙并非所有人都熟知，因此，有些翻译者可能需要使用描述性的短语，例如“控制门开关的物件”。有时可以从钥匙的功能角度来翻译，例如“开锁器”或“打开锁的工具”。</p>\n<p>除了<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:25\">JDG 3:25</a> ，上面所有提到“钥匙”的经文都是象征性的。然而，我们查阅的所有译本仍然全部使用了“钥匙”这个词。请注意，<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Italian Common Language Version\">ITCL</abbr> 在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:22\">ISA 22:22</a> 中扩展了译文；原文文本的字面意思是“我必将大卫家的钥匙放在他的肩上”（如<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 的译法），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Italian Common Language Version\">ITCL</abbr> 的意大利文本意思是：“大卫宫殿中的所有权柄都必赐给他，钥匙必交给他掌管。”<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Living Translation\">NLT</abbr> 的译法类似，英文意为：“我必把大卫家的钥匙——王宫中最高的职位——赐给他。”</p>\n<p>有些时候，可能无法采用“某个地方的钥匙”这种表述，例如<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:1\">REV 9:1</a> 中的“深渊”（“the abyss”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ），或<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:19\">MAT 16:19</a> 中的“天国”（“the kingdom of heaven”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> ）。在这些情况下，翻译者可能需要说“……的入口的钥匙”，或者“用来打开或关闭……的门的钥匙”。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
